The Commission received several comments to rule G-37 recommending that the rule provide an exemption process,
based on the dealer's compliance procedures and supervision, for certain inadvertent violations.
 The Commission approved the rule and recommended the MSRB separately address these concerns by filing a proposed
rule change that provides an exemption process for inadvertent violations. The MSRB's proposal adequately addresses
these concerns.
 The proposal provides procedures for dealers to obtain exemptive relief from rule G-37's prohibition on business
where, for example, covered persons inadvertently make contributions that slightly exceed the 

de minimis 

exemption provided by the rule. The proposal's exemptive relief is based on the dealers' supervision of covered persons,
compliance procedures concerning rule G-37, and corrective and remedial action concerning inadvertent violations.
